Hello, everyone!
I’ve been trying to create a task and associate it with both a deal and a company using the HubSpot API v3. I’m making a POST request to the following endpoint: <https://api.hubapi.com/crm/v3/objects/tasks>
Here’s the JSON payload I’m sending:
```{
    "properties": {
        "hs_timestamp": "2019-10-30T03:30:17.883Z",
        "hs_task_body": "Send Proposal",
        "HubSpot_owner_id": "1234",
        "hs_task_subject": "Follow-up for Brian Buyer",
        "hs_task_status": "WAITING",
        "hs_task_priority": "HIGH"
    },
    "associations": [
      {
        "to": {
          "id": "123444",
          "type": "deal"
        },
        "type": "task_to_deal"
      }
    ]
}```
The task is created successfully, but it doesn’t have any associations. I expected the task to be associated with the specified deal.
Could anyone help me understand what I might be doing wrong?
